In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney addresses several topics including the nomination of Chuck Hagel for Secretary of Defense, the importance of diversity in the President's Cabinet, and the upcoming debt ceiling debate. Carney defends Hagel's record on Israel and Iran, stating that he has been a staunch supporter of Israel and a supporter of the sanctions against Iran. Carney also mentions that the President believes in diversity and chooses the best person for the job, regardless of gender or race. In regards to the debt ceiling debate, Carney emphasizes that the President will not negotiate with Congress over raising the debt ceiling and that it is Congress's responsibility to pay the bills that they have incurred.